Rating: 4
I just made this. Delicious! And quite easy. Very nice flavors. Based on the other reviews, I upped the spices. So although I halved the recipe, I kept the spices about the same: 1tsp garam masala, 1 tsp coriander, 1 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp curry. I definitely salted and peppered liberally- when cooking the onions, when blending the marsala, and then at the end. This does make a lot of sauce. I didn't use all of it, and could have added some spinach too to the dish and still had plenty. I'm not sure if it's because I was using lite coconut milk, but that kind of watered it down a little too much for my taste. Maybe next time, I'll use full fat coconut milk or use a little bit less of the lite. I'm also not sure if the lemon added much because it's a little sour anyway from the yoghurt. Could probably do without that. But I'll definitely make this again!

