Rating: 2
I would make this again but I would consider making a few changes to cooking the shrimp. I would saute the shrimp and any other vegetables you're going to use first and then remove them. Don't cook the shrimp all the way through because they will continue to cook when you take them off and will cook more when you add them back in. I would then add only the coconut milk (1/2 or the full can) and reduce it. After it has reduced for a good while, add the masala mixture and reduce a bit more. When everything (else) is almost done, add the shrimp (and veggies) back in to reheat them and then... serve.

