Rating: 3
I just don't see how anyone could not like this. It is fabulous, and I would have given it 4 stars if I hadn't needed to double the spices. The masala seems to be spiced to perfection before it's added to the coconut milk... It gets significantly weaker once it's added to the final mixture.I've made this with both chicken and shrimp, and I really prefer the chicken. I cut it into rather small cubes and let it simmer in the sauce for about 20 minutes. This helps the chicken to really absorb the flavor, and it's something that can't be done with the shrimp, because they'd obviously be too tough if they cooked for that long.A few reviewers suggested draining the tomatoes or leaving some of them whole... I wouldn't recommend this. The recipe is of the perfect consistency when made as-is, and the tomatoes and their sauce are a vital part of the flavor of this dish, as are the ground coriander, lemon juice, and cilantro. If you omit any of these ingredients, you're doing the recipe a serious injustice. Make sure you use good quality curry powder, and, most importanly, enjoy this amazing Indian dish!!

