This is a wonderful dish. Previous reviews of this recipe were helpful. Here's what I learned: 1.) The recipe makes A LOT of sauce (masala). I made all the sauce & used only 1/2 for dinner. I froze the other half. 2). To finish the recipe, I used one of the smaller cans of coconut milk (to go with the 1/2 sauce). 3.) I increased the spices, with the exception of the cayenne (which I actually decreased by half). 4.) One reviewer suggested using chicken instead of shrimp - I have to agree. The sauce is so intensely flavored that you really can't taste the shrimp. 5.) Other reviewers commented on the ease of preparation. They are right! Once you make the masala, the last part of the meal is basically a brief saute, addition of all pre-prepped ingredients, and heating. Make sure you have something to do in your kitchen for the 20-30 minutes it takes to brown the onions in the masala.

