This was tasty. Making the sauce ahead of time really improves its flavor. Don't add the shrimp until the last minute, though-- they'll become rubbery if they're reheated. Very simple recipe, with yummy results. I served this with white basmati rice.

Rating: 4
This recipe is really wonderful. Making the masala sauce the day before makes it a snap for entertaining, as it's very quick to prepare. I've made it twice with lite coconut milk (unsweetened) and with brown basmati rice - rave reviews!!!

Rating: 4
This is a great recipe. I have made it twice. The first time I used the regular unsweetened coconut milk, which (I think) has a high fat content. The second time I made it with lite coconut milk, brown rice and even cut back on the oil a bit. It was still great.